5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-warning-ai-could-eliminate-jobs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Big%20Tech%20invest%20billions%20in%20developing%20state-of-the-art%20large-language%20models%2C%20a%20small%20group%20of%20AI%20researchers%20is%20working%20on%20the%20next%20big%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComputer%20scientists%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-board-member-former-google-ai-fei-fei-li-maven-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFei-Fei%20Li%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Stanford%20professor%20famous%20for%20inventing%20ImageNet%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-yann-lecun-deepseek-open-source-openai-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EYann%20LeCun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Meta's%20chief%20AI%20scientist%2C%20are%20building%20what%20they%20call%20%26quot%3Bworld%20models.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-ai-dictionary-help-understand-nvidia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elarge-language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20determine%20outputs%20based%20on%20statistical%20relationships%20between%20the%20words%20and%20phrases%20in%20their%20training%20data%2C%20world%20models%20predict%20events%20based%20on%20the%20mental%20constructs%20that%20humans%20make%20of%20the%20world%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLanguage%20doesn't%20exist%20in%20nature%2C%26quot%3B%20Li%20said%20on%20a%20recent%20episode%20of%20Andreessen%20Horowitz's%20a16z%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BHumans%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20do%20we%20survive%2C%20live%2C%20and%20work%2C%20but%20we%20build%20civilization%20beyond%20language.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComputer%20scientist%20and%20MIT%20professor%2C%20Jay%20Wright%20Forrester%2C%20in%20his%201971%20paper%20%26quot%3BCounterintuitive%20Behavior%20of%20Social%20Systems%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20why%20mental%20models%20are%20crucial%20to%20human%20behavior%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EEach%20of%20us%20uses%20models%20constantly.%20Every%20person%20in%20private%20life%20and%20in%20business%20instinctively%20uses%20models%20for%20decision%20making.%20The%20mental%20images%20in%20one's%20head%20about%20one's%20surroundings%20are%20models.%20One's%20head%20does%20not%20contain%20real%20families%2C%20businesses%2C%20cities%2C%20governments%2C%20or%20countries.%20One%20uses%20selected%20concepts%20and%20relationships%20to%20represent%20real%20systems.%20A%20mental%20image%20is%20a%20model.%20All%20decisions%20are%20taken%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20models.%20All%20laws%20are%20passed%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20models.%20All%20executive%20actions%20are%20taken%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20models.%20The%20question%20is%20not%20to%20use%20or%20ignore%20models.%20The%20question%20is%20only%20a%20choice%20among%20alternative%20models.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20AI%20is%20to%20meet%20or%20surpass%20human%20intelligence%2C%20then%20the%20researchers%20behind%20it%20believe%20it%20should%20be%20able%20to%20make%20mental%20models%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELi%20has%20been%20working%20on%20this%20through%20World%20Labs%2C%20which%20she%20cofounded%20in%202024%20with%20an%20initial%20backing%20of%20%24230%20million%20from%20venture%20firms%20like%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%2C%20New%20Enterprise%20Associates%2C%20and%20Radical%20Ventures.%20%26quot%3BWe%20aim%20to%20lift%20AI%20models%20from%20the%202D%20plane%20of%20pixels%20to%20full%203D%20worlds%20%E2%80%94%20both%20virtual%20and%20real%20%E2%80%94%20endowing%20them%20with%20spatial%20intelligence%20as%20rich%20as%20our%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20World%20Labs%20says%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELi%20said%20on%20the%20No%20Priors%20podcast%20that%20spatial%20intelligence%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ability%20to%20understand%2C%20reason%2C%20interact%2C%20and%20generate%203D%20worlds%2C%26quot%3B%20given%20that%20the%20world%20is%20fundamentally%20three-dimensional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELi%20said%20she%20sees%20applications%20for%20world%20models%20in%20creative%20fields%2C%20robotics%2C%20or%20any%20area%20that%20warrants%20infinite%20universes.%20Like%20Meta%2C%20Anduril%2C%20and%20other%20Silicon%20Valley%20heavyweights%2C%20that%20could%20mean%20advances%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-cto-time-for-silicon-valley-embrace-military-again-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emilitary%20applications%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20helping%20those%20on%20the%20battlefield%20better%20perceive%20their%20surroundings%20and%20anticipate%20their%20enemies'%20next%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20of%20building%20world%20models%20is%20the%20paucity%20of%20sufficient%20data.%20In%20contrast%20to%20language%2C%20which%20humans%20have%20refined%20and%20documented%20over%20centuries%2C%20spatial%20intelligence%20is%20less%20developed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20ask%20you%20to%20close%20your%20eyes%20right%20now%20and%20draw%20out%20or%20build%20a%203D%20model%20of%20the%20environment%20around%20you%2C%20it's%20not%20that%20easy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20on%20the%20No%20Priors%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20that%20much%20capability%20to%20generate%20extremely%20complicated%20models%20till%20we%20get%20trained.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20gather%20the%20data%20necessary%20for%20these%20models%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20require%20more%20and%20more%20sophisticated%20data%20engineering%2C%20data%20acquisition%2C%20data%20processing%2C%20and%20data%20synthesis%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20the%20challenge%20of%20building%20a%20believable%20world%20even%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Meta%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-yann-lecun-ai-models-lack-4-key-human-traits-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echief%20AI%20scientist%20Yann%20LeCun%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20a%20small%20team%20dedicated%20to%20a%20similar%20project.%20The%20team%20uses%20video%20data%20to%20train%20models%20and%20runs%20simulations%20that%20abstract%20the%20videos%20at%20different%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20basic%20idea%20is%20that%20you%20don't%20predict%20at%20the%20pixel%20level.%20You%20train%20a%20system%20to%20run%20an%20abstract%20representation%20of%20the%20video%20so%20that%20you%20can%20make%20predictions%20in%20that%20abstract%20representation%2C%20and%20hopefully%20this%20representation%20will%20eliminate%20all%20the%20details%20that%20cannot%20be%20predicted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20AI%20Action%20Summit%20in%20Paris%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20creates%20a%20simpler%20set%20of%20building%20blocks%20for%20mapping%20out%20trajectories%20for%20how%20the%20world%20will%20change%20at%20a%20particular%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-yann-lecun-scaling-ai-wont-make-it-smarter-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELeCun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20Li%2C%20believes%20these%20models%20are%20the%20only%20way%20to%20create%20truly%20intelligent%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20AI%20systems%20that%20can%20learn%20new%20tasks%20really%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20recently%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore.%20%26quot%3BThey%20need%20to%20understand%20the%20physical%20world%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20text%20and%20language%20but%20the%20real%20world%20%E2%80%94%20have%20some%20level%20of%20common%20sense%2C%20and%20abilities%20to%20reason%20and%20plan%2C%20have%20persistent%20memory%20%E2%80%94%20all%20the%20stuff%20that%20we%20expect%20from%20intelligent%20entities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-model-ai-explained-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749809702000%2