%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fdan-ives%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDan%20Ives%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tech%20and%20AI%20permabull%20who%20can%20often%20be%20found%20on%20CNBC%20wearing%20fluorescent%20blazers%20%E2%80%94%20who%20has%20parlayed%20his%20bold%20analyst%20calls%20into%20the%20Wedbush%20AI%20Revolution%20ETF%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fdan-ives-wedbush-ai-revolution-etf-us9479131099%3FmiRedirects%3D2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIVES%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20let's%20not%20forget%20Fundstrat's%20Tom%20Lee%20%E2%80%94%20former%20chief%20equity%20strategist%20at%20JPMorgan%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20Granny%20Shots%20US%20Large%20Cap%20ETF%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Ffundstrat-granny-shots-us-large-etf-us8863642315%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGRNY%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey've%20stepped%20into%20a%20crowded%20market%20with%20thousands%20of%20funds%20competing%20for%20investors'%20money.%20A%20record%20723%20ETFs%20came%20to%20market%20in%202024%20alone.%20And%20they're%20using%20their%20own%20high-profile%20personal%20brands%20to%20stand%20out%20in%20a%20crowded%20marketplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20starting%20a%20fund%20is%20an%20entirely%20different%20beast%20than%20keeping%20one%20afloat%20for%20any%20sustained%20amount%20of%20time.%20Yes%2C%20strong%20performance%20is%20crucial.%20But%20running%20a%20fund%20is%20expensive%2C%20and%20it%20takes%20much%20more%20than%20good%20returns%20to%20ensure%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20start%2C%20the%20cost%20to%20launch%20a%20fund%20is%20hefty.%20Firms%20are%20looking%20at%20a%20%2450%2C000-to-%24100%2C000%20filing%20fee%20with%20the%20SEC%2C%20according%20to%20Zachary%20Evans%2C%20analyst%20for%20passive%20strategies%20at%20Morningstar.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etf.com%2Fsections%2Fnews%2Flaunching-etf-no-cheap-endeavor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EETF.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20puts%20that%20number%20between%20%24100%2C000%20and%20%24500%2C000.%20Depending%20on%20the%20type%20of%20fund%2C%20there%20also%20may%20be%20an%20initial%20listing%20fee%20with%20NYSE%20or%20Nasdaq.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bills%20don't%20stop%20there.%20Listing%20fees%20with%20the%20exchange%20come%20due%20every%20year.%20With%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasdaq.com%2Fsolutions%2Fnasdaq-etf-listings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENasdaq%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20it's%20a%20%244%2C000%20annual%20fee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20a%20long%20list%20of%20costs%20associated%20with%20running%20the%20fund%20itself%2C%20Evans%20said.%20Paying%20the%20staff%20who%20execute%20the%20trades.%20Paying%20compliance%20and%20a%20risk-management%20team.%20Paying%20sales%20and%20advertising%20teams%20to%20market%20the%20fund.%20Paying%20rent%20for%20your%20office%20space.%20And%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20adds%20up%2C%20and%20it%20means%20funds%20need%20to%20amass%20significant%20assets%20under%20management.%20ETF%20providers%20make%20money%20through%20the%20annual%20fees%2C%20or%20expense%20ratios%2C%20they%20charge%20investors.%20So%20the%20more%20money%20they%20manage%2C%20the%20more%20money%20they're%20bringing%20in.%20Performance%20also%20plays%20a%20role%20here%20%E2%80%94%20if%20a%20fund's%20value%20rises%20by%2020%25%20in%20a%20year%2C%20the%20fees%20it%20extracts%20will%20be%2020%25%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20can%20vary%20quite%20a%20bit%2C%20but%20a%20baseline%20number%20we've%20heard%20is%20that%20it%20should%20cost%20around%20%24200%2C000%20a%20year%20to%20run%20an%20ETF%2C%26quot%3B%20Evans%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BMore%20complicated%20strategies%20will%20cost%20more%2C%20simpler%20strategies%20will%20cost%20less%2C%20or%20if%20it's%20from%20a%20large%20firm%20that%20has%20economies%20of%20scale%2C%20it%20might%20cost%20less%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BSay%20an%20ETF%20charges%2050%20basis%20points%20with%20annual%20expenses%20of%20%24200%2C000%20a%20year.%20You%20need%20%2440%20million%20AUM%20in%20order%20to%20break%20even%20on%20that%20product.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20funds%2C%20there's%20also%20pressure%20associated%20with%20seed%20money.%20When%20an%20ETF%20launches%2C%20Evans%20said%20it%20might%20have%20some%20investors%20who%20promise%20to%20keep%20their%20capital%20locked%20up%20in%20the%20fund%20for%20a%20set%20period%20of%20time%20%E2%80%94%20say%20two%20or%20three%20years.%20Once%20that%20period%20ends%2C%20if%20the%20investors%20pull%20their%20money%2C%20it%20can%20be%20an%20existential%20threat%20to%20a%20fund%20if%20they%20haven't%20pulled%20in%20enough%20money%20from%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20that%20seed%20money%20dries%20up%2C%20in%20order%20for%20them%20to%20endure%2C%20they%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20have%20enough%20investor%20interest%2C%20enough%20assets%20to%20sustain%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Evans%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFund%20closures%20are%20increasingly%20common.%20Evans%20said%20a%20little%20more%20than%20200%20closed%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20a%20record%20%E2%80%94%20and%20just%20under%20200%20closed%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20more%20companies%20are%20launching%20their%20products%2C%20more%20companies%20are%20closing%20down%20their%20products%20%E2%80%94%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20which%20have%20really%20failed%20to%20catch%20on%20with%20investors%2C%26quot%3B%20Evans%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20failed%20to%20generate%20either%20the%20performance%20or%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20the%20asset%20level%20to%20support%20these%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-money-does-new-etf-need-to-succeed-aum-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749809101000%2