20ChatGPT%2C%20feeding%20all%20the%20data%20back%20to%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20managers%20wrote%20in%20detail%20how%20ChatGPT's%20answers%20tended%20to%20have%20better%20formatting%20and%20more%20interesting%20facts.%20They%20ordered%20workers%20to%20%26quot%3Bexplain%20why%20gpt4%20is%20better%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bmake%20it%20BETTER%20than%20GPT.%26quot%3B%20A%20single%20spreadsheet%20flagged%20dozens%20of%20contractors%20for%20writing%20responses%20%26quot%3Bconsistently%20worse%20than%20GPT4.%26quot%3B%20In%20one%20instance%2C%20the%20document%20said%20contractors%20could%20get%20a%2015%25%20bonus%20for%20their%20responses%20performing%20better%20than%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20is%20a%20San%20Francisco%20startup%20that%20does%20crucial%20AI%20grunt%20work%20for%20Big%20Tech.%20It%20uses%20an%20army%20of%20human%20contractors%20to%20do%20things%20like%20labeling%20images%20and%2C%20as%20was%20the%20case%20with%20Google%2C%20rewriting%20chatbot%20responses.%20Meta%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D2e730608c25b680d1eb27667fb72bf8438fcc2fd144ae834d4533306be08415c%26postID%3D6848b02f7ee75c80592f8c24%26postSlug%3Dgoogle-used-chatgpt-to-improve-bard-scale-ai-documents-2025-6%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.theinformation.com%252Farticles%252Fmeta-pay-nearly-15-billion-scale-ai-stake-startups-28-year-old-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0investing%20%2415%20billion%20in%20Scale%20AI%20as%20part%20of%20a%20blockbuster%20AI%20deal%20to%20buy%20almost%20half%20the%20company%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scale-ai-15-billion-alexandr-wang-acquihire-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20hire%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0its%20CEO%2C%20Alexandr%20Wang%2C%20for%20an%20in-house%20%26quot%3Bsuperintelligence%26quot%3B%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20documents%20obtained%20by%20BI%20showcase%20how%20closely%20Google%20monitored%20its%20chief%20rival's%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20terms%20of%20service%20at%20the%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fpolicies%2Frow-terms-of-use%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprohibited%3C%2Fa%3E%20others%20from%20using%20its%20output%20%26quot%3Bto%20develop%20models%20that%20compete%20with%20OpenAI.%26quot%3B%20Scale%20AI%20and%20Google%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20question%20about%20whether%20they%20got%20permission%20from%20OpenAI%20for%20these%20detailed%20comparisons%20and%20rewrites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20ChatGPT%20outputs%20weren't%20used%20to%20train%20Google's%20or%20any%20others'%20models%20and%20were%20part%20of%20routine%20%26quot%3Bevaluations%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20it%20said%20are%20industry%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScale%20did%20not%2C%20and%20does%20not%2C%20use%20ChatGPT%20responses%20to%20train%20Gemini%20or%20any%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Scale%20AI%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20The%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20documents%20describe%20%26quot%3Bstandard%20side-by-side%20evaluations%2C%20not%20the%20use%20of%20ChatGPT%20or%20any%20third-party%20model%20outputs%20for%20training.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoing%20side-by-side%20competitive%20evals%20is%20standard%20practice%20for%20the%20industry%20and%20those%20evaluation%20results%20are%20not%20used%20to%20train%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Google%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAny%20suggestion%20that%20we%20have%20used%20other%20companies'%20models%20to%20train%20Gemini%20is%20inaccurate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20told%20BI%20that%20this%20kind%20of%20comparison%20is%20indeed%20common%20at%20some%20top%20AI%20labs.%20Open%20AI%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fretail-consumer%2Fopenai-taps-google-unprecedented-cloud-deal-despite-ai-rivalry-sources-say-2025-06-10%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20partnership%20talks%20with%20Google%20Cloud%2C%20didn't%20respond%20to%20repeated%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e2009aa-aea1-45ed-adfc-de2c64df9509%5C%22%3EProject%20'Bulba'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20gave%20Bard%20a%20catchy%20codename%2C%20%26quot%3BBulba%2C%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20Bulbasaur.%20The%20mission%20was%20clear%3A%20compare%20Bulba's%20answers%20with%20ChatGPT's%20to%20make%20them%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20never%20mentioned%20Google%20by%20name%20in%20the%20documents%2C%20referring%20instead%20to%20its%20anonymous%20%26quot%3Bclient.%26quot%3B%20It%20references%20Bard%20over%20a%20dozen%20times%20in%20a%20private%20Google%20sheet%20titled%20%26quot%3Bbard%20rewrite%20comparison%20with%20gpt4%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20slide%20in%20one%20training%20document%20includes%20Google's%20logo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alexandr%20Wang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684ae50ef748d8c055f38f41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScale%20AI%20founder%20Alexandr%20Wang.%3Cp%3EJeff%20Chiu%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%20a%20manager%20ordered%20workers%20to%20study%20GPT-4's%20responses%20closely%20and%20figure%20out%20why%20they%20outperformed%20Bard's.%20%26quot%3BTry%20to%20come%20up%20with%20feedback%20that%20we%20can%20share%20so%20that%20experts%20can%20write%20responses%20better%20than%20GPT4%20or%20at%20least%20the%20same%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20manager%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20also%20created%20a%20spreadsheet%20that%20compared%201%2C729%20Bard%20rewrites%20directly%20to%20ChatGPT%20in%20October%202023.%20Each%20rewrite%20was%20rated%20with%20labels%20like%20%26quot%3Bworse%20than%20GPT4%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BNeeds%20Some%20Fixes.%26quot%3B%20In%20one%20example%2C%20a%20worker%20rewrote%20a%20Bard%20review%20of%20a%20nursery%20chair%20that%20managers%20stamped%20%26quot%3Bworse%20than%20GPT%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20%26quot%3Blacks%20detail%20compared%20to%20GPT4.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20contractor's%20review%20of%20a%20Charleston%20history%20museum%20didn't%20make%20the%20cut%20either%20%E2%80%94%20a%20manager%20wrote%20that%20ChatGPT's%20version%20was%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20also%20used%20ChatGPT%20to%20improve%20Bard's%20responses%20in%20specific%20domains%2C%20like%20engineering%20or%20physics.%20In%20an%20update%20from%20August%202023%2C%20Scale%20AI%20managers%20wrote%20that%20they%20would%20have%20staff%20%26quot%3Bredo%26quot%3B%20Google's%20AI%20answers%20for%20engineering-related%20questions%20%26quot%3Bwith%20GPT4%20guidance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20documents%20showed%20that%20Scale%20AI%20and%20Google%20barred%20its%20contractors%20from%20copying%20and%20pasting%20ChatGPT%20responses%20directly%20into%20their%20rewrites%2C%20though%2C%20an%20issue%20many%20contractors%20were%20flagged%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22caa97434-8d1b-4312-86b9-e9da67836b3c%5C%22%3EScale%20AI%20says%20comparisons%20weren't%20for%20training%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internal%20documents%20BI%20reviewed%20described%20the%20project's%20goal%20as%20helping%20%26quot%3Btrain%26quot%3B%20Bard%20to%20give%20it%20more%20specific%20and%20complete%20answers%2C%20and%20refer%20to%20efforts%20to%20%26quot%3Bimprove%20the%20model.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20did%20not%20answer%20follow-up%20questions%20on%20whether%20those%20comparisons%20influenced%20training.%20Scale%20AI%20said%20that%20there's%20a%20clear%20line%20between%20evaluating%20a%20model's%20performance%20and%20training%20it%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20ChatGPT%20outputs%20were%20only%20used%20for%20the%20former.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20difference%20between%20training%20data%20and%20evaluation%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BEvaluation%20data%20is%20not%20ingested%20by%20a%20model%20to%20train%20it%2C%20but%20rather%20used%20to%20measure%20how%20well%20a%20model%20is%20performing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Guzdial%2C%20an%20assistant%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alberta%2C%20says%20evaluation%20data%20can%20still%20influence%20an%20AI%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20all%20they're%20doing%20is%20looking%20at%20those%20outputs%20and%20rating%20that%20information%20to%20adjust%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20model%2C%20you%20could%20still%20make%20the%20argument%20that%20it's%20involved%20in%20the%20training%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252c72124-a0a8-4929-8767-86caccd2ee6c%5C%22%3EThe%20documents%20were%20left%20public%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%2C%20which%20has%20not%20previously%20made%20public%20details%20about%20its%20work%20with%20Google%2C%20left%20an%20over%20300-page%20Google%20Doc%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20contains%20dozens%20of%20links%20to%20other%20Google%20Docs%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20also%20public%20and%20contain%20sensitive%20information%2C%20including%20contractors'%20compensation%20details%2C%20personal%20email%20addresses%2C%20and%20performance%20reviews%2C%20along%20with%20still-functioning%20passwords%20to%20internal%20training%20sessions.%20Some%20of%20the%20Google%20Docs%20can%20still%20be%20edited%20by%20anyone%20who%20has%20the%20link.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScale%20AI%20told%20BI%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bactively%20investigating%26quot%3B%20how%20the%20document%20%26quot%3Bmay%20have%20been%20accessed%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Btaking%20steps%20to%20ensure%20any%20inadvertent%20exposure%20is%20remediated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20two%20days%20after%20BI%20told%20Scale%20AI%20about%20the%20public%20Google%20Doc%2C%20it%20was%20still%20online%20and%20available%20for%20anyone%20with%20the%20link%20to%20download.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b565f0f-0915-4462-88eb-6801c0426537%5C%22%3EGoogle%20is%20ahead%20on%20AI%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225765%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682756503fe8d39283661154%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223843%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai.%3Cp%3EKlaudia%20Radecka%2FNurPhoto%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20documents%20don't%20specify%20how%20effective%20the%20comparison%20efforts%20were.%20Since%20its%20Bard%20flub%20in%202023%2C%20Google%20has%20rebranded%20Bard%20to%20Gemini%20and%20transformed%20into%20an%20AI%20shipping%20machine.%20Last%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2025-06-08%2Fmeta-in-talks-for-scale-ai-investment-that-could-top-10-billion%3Fembedded-checkout%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20launched%20over%20100%3C%2Fa%3E%20new%20AI%20products%20and%20features%20at%20I%2FO%2C%20its%20annual%20developer%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20began%20his%20speech%20at%20I%2FO%20by%20rattling%20off%20the%20industry%20benchmarks%20that%20Gemini%20is%20topping%2C%20touting%20the%20company's%20latest%20AI%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20shipping%20faster%20than%20ever%2C%26quot%3B%20Pichai%20said%20onstage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acrollet%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ecrollet%40insider.co%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cu%3Em%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20and%20WhatsApp%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22tel%3A6282822811%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3E628-282-2811%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%