ads%2F2025%2F06%2Fthalassemia--1749549115-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fthalassemia--1749549115-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-447117%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThalassemia%20and%20Sickle%20Cell%20Society%20(TSCS)%20is%20a%20registered%20NGO%20established%20in%20the%20year%201998%20with%20the%20pledge%20to%20help%20thalassemia%20patients%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tscsindia.org%2Fwho-we-are%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETSCS%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSeeing%20is%20believing.%20So%20we%20put%20these%20parents%20in%20touch%20with%20other%20parents%20whose%20children%20have%20been%20battling%20thalassemia%20and%20who%20can%20vouch%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F413803%2Fgoa-blood-samaritan-mario-fernandes-100-donations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblood%20transfusion%20helps%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%20A%20conversation%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20a%20better%20understanding.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20parent%20sees%20their%20child%20feel%20better%20after%20a%20blood%20transfusion%2C%20they%20begin%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20the%20right%20treatment%2C%E2%80%9D%20Agarwal%20notes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20area%20where%20misunderstanding%20is%20rampant%20is%20the%20chelation%20therapy.%20A%20corollary%20of%20successive%20blood%20transfusions%20is%20the%20build-up%20of%20iron%20in%20the%20body.%20The%20excess%20iron%20needs%20to%20be%20removed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmphasising%20the%20importance%20of%20chelation%2C%20Dr%20Suman%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20absolutely%20important%20for%20the%20iron%20that%20is%20coming%20along%20with%20the%20blood%20being%20transfused%20to%20be%20removed.%20The%20serum%20ferritin%20needs%20to%20be%20less%20than%201000%20ng%2FmL%2C%20but%20nearly%2020-25%20percent%20of%20our%20patients%E2%80%99%20parents%20do%20not%20understand%20this.%20One%20round%20of%20counselling%20is%20not%20enough%2C%20and%20so%20we%20repeatedly%20tell%20them%20to%20get%20the%20iron%20chelation%20done.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%227521127830%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20ways%20to%20chelate%20the%20iron.%20One%20is%20oral%20methods%20%E2%80%94%20tablets%20ingested%20%E2%80%94%20or%20subcutaneous%20injections.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20first%20advise%20oral%20drugs%2C%20only%20if%20the%20iron%20levels%20are%20not%20being%20controlled%2C%20we%20start%20the%20child%20on%20injectables.%20The%20half-life%20of%20the%20drug%20in%20an%20injectable%20is%20short%2C%20and%20so%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20in%20the%20body%20for%20at%20least%2010%20hours.%20We%20monitor%20the%20serum%20iron%20levels%20every%20three%20months%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Suman%20adds.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20food%20restrictions%2C%20she%20does%20not%20advise%20her%20patients%20on%20any%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F208525%2Fblood-donation-tips-precautions-health-myths-busted-by-doctor-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edietary%20modifications%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20tell%20them%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20meats%20and%20foods%20rich%20in%20iron.%20But%20considering%20that%20the%20major%20reason%20for%20iron%20build-up%20is%20the%20blood%20transfusion%20%E2%80%94%20every%20transfusion%20introduces%20200%20mg%20of%20iron%20in%20the%20body%20%E2%80%94%20diet%20does%20not%20make%20a%20big%20difference.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EScreening%20%26amp%3B%20testing%3A%20A%20way%20to%20future-proof%20India%20against%20thalassemia%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20kinds%20of%20thalassemias%3A%20thalassemia%20major%2C%20thalassemia%20intermedia%2C%20and%20thalassemia%20minor.%20People%20born%20with%20thalassemia%20major%20and%20the%20severe%20form%20of%20thalassemia%20intermedia%20require%20lifelong%20blood%20transfusions%20and%20iron%20chelation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20born%20with%20thalassemia%20minor%20are%20clinically%20normal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20conversation%20is%20slowly%20shifting%20to%20how%20the%20number%20of%20thalassemia%20major%20patients%20can%20be%20reduced.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Manoj%20Jhalani%2C%20former%20mission%20director%20of%20National%20Health%20Mission%2C%20points%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CApproximately%2030%20million%20people%20are%20silent%20carriers%20for%20%E1%BA%9E-thalassemia%20in%20our%20country%20and%20live%20a%20normal%20life%2C%20but%20the%20marriage%20between%20two%20silent%20carriers%20may%20result%20in%20their%20children%20having%20a%20serious%20disease%2C%20requiring%20regular%20blood%20transfusion%20for%20survival.%20Since%20only%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20patients%20can%20be%20cured%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F176715%2Ftamil-nadu-woman-is-india-first-female-bone-marrow-donor%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebone%20marrow%20transplantation%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20HLA-identical%20donors%2C%20prevention%20of%20the%20birth%20of%20an%20affected%20child%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20most%20feasible%20and%20cost-effective%20approach%20for%20control%20of%20this%20disease.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20720px)%20100vw%2C%20720px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FScreenshot-2025-06-10-151417-1749548688.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20genetic%20transmission%20of%20thalassemia%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FScreenshot-2025-06-10-151417-1749548688.jpg%20720w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FScreenshot-2025-06-10-151417-1749548688-300x239.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FScreenshot-2025-06-10-151417-1749548688-500x399.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FScreenshot-2025-06-10-151417-1749548688-150x120.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-447111%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20genetic%20transmission%20of%20thalassemia%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsickle.nhm.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fguidelines%2FNHM_Guidelines_on_Hemoglobinopathies_in_India.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Health%20Mission%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Health%20Mission%20recommends%20carrier%20screening%2C%20genetic%20counselling%2C%20and%20prenatal%20diagnosis%20as%20a%20preventative%20approach.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20TSCS%2C%20led%20by%20Agarwal%2C%20steps%20in.%20A%202022%20study%20by%20Genome%20Foundation%20and%20the%20Thalassemia%20and%20Sickle%20Cell%20Society%20(TSCS)%20found%20that%20four%20districts%20in%20Telangana%20were%20driving%20the%20average%20for%20high%20risk%20of%20Beta-Thalassemia.%20One%20of%20these%20was%20Mahabubnagar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWould%20you%20believe%20that%20today%2C%20Mahbubnagar%20is%20leading%20the%20way%20in%20thalassemia%20control%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgarwal%20explains%20how%2C%20following%20an%20MoU%20signed%20with%20the%20Collector%20of%20Mahbubnagar%20in%202022%2C%20100%20percent%20pre-natal%20screening%20was%20done.%20This%20means%20that%20every%20year%2C%20since%202022%2C%20every%20pregnant%20woman%20in%20Mahabubnagar%20has%20been%20screened%20%E2%80%94%20Agarwal%20credits%20the%20ASHA%20workers%20for%20this%20assistance%20%E2%80%94%20to%20check%20for%20thalassemia%20carriers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20pregnant%20mother%20is%20found%20to%20be%20a%20carrier%20of%20the%20thalassemia%20gene%2C%20the%20father%20is%20tested.%20If%20he%20too%20is%20found%20to%20be%20a%20carrier%2C%20the%20foetus%20is%20tested%2C%20and%20if%20found%20to%20be%20thalassemia%20major%2C%20the%20next%20step%20is%20counselling.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20counsel%20the%20to-be%20parents%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F208322%2Fbengaluru-teen-teacher-death-blood-donation-community-inspiring-india-say143%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20lifetime%20of%20blood%20transfusions%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20child%20will%20have%20to%20have%2C%20the%20difficulties%20of%20growing%20up%20with%20thalassemia%2C%20etc%2C%E2%80%9D%20Agarwal%20explains.%20The%20focus%20is%20on%20giving%20parents%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20make%20an%20informed%20decision%20about%20whether%20to%20carry%20on%20with%20the%20pregnancy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20former%20district%20collector%20of%20Mahbubnagar%20(wishing%20to%20remain%20anonymous)%20has%20commended%20the%20%E2%80%9Cextraordinary%20impact%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20project.%20Now%2C%20TSCS%20is%20looking%20to%20clone%20the%20model%20across%20India%E2%80%99s%20districts%20with%20government%20approval.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETesting%20is%20a%20pragmatic%20necessity%2C%20Agarwal%20shares%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20only%20expectant%20parents%20who%20must%20be%20screened%2C%20but%20also%20families%20where%20there%20is%20a%20thalassemia%20major%20person.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20case%20of%20a%20person%20with%20thalassemia%20major%2C%20we%20screened%2078%20family%20members%20of%20theirs%2C%20and%2027%20percent%20were%20found%20to%20be%20thalassemia%20minors.%E2%80%9D%20Early%20screening%20means%20early%20detection%2C%20which%20can%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20early%20counselling%20and%20thus%20a%20preventative%20approach.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20well%20be%20the%20contingency%20plan%20India%20needs%20to%20curb%20its%20thalassemia%20numbers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20until%20then%2C%20your%20blood%20donation%20could%20save%20a%20child%20struggling%20with%20thalassemia.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20World%20Blood%20Donor%20Day%2C%20if%20you%E2%80%99d%20like%20to%20step%20in%20and%20help%20a%20child%2C%20check%20out%20the%20various%20camps%20TSCS%20is%20having%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tscsindia.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Khushi%20Arora%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetailm.aspx%3FPRID%3D1841433%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVice%20President%20calls%20for%20focus%20on%20preventive%20measures%20to%20address%20the%20huge%20burden%20of%20genetic%20diseases%20in%20the%20country%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20Press%20Information%20Bureau%2C%20Published%20on%2014%20July%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%